  "original_title": "\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0dbd\u0db1\u0dd2\u0db4 \u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf \u0dc3\u0d82\u0dc1\u0ddd\u0db0\u0db1\u0dba\u0da7: \u0dad\u0dc4\u0db1\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dd0\u0dba\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dc5 \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0d89\u0dc0\u0dad\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lankan Constitution Amendment: The request to issue a ban is dismissed",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Colombo District Judge Purnima Paranagama today (02) refused to issue an interim injunction to prevent the adoption of constitutional amendments proposed to be made in relation to the party's chairmanship at the All-Ceylon Committee meeting of the Sri Lanka Freedom Party.",
        "After considering the facts related to a petition submitted by Sri Lanka Freedom Party executive member Mr. Montague Sarachchandra, requesting to prevent the adoption of the proposed constitutional amendments related to the position of the party's chairman in the forthcoming meeting of the party's All-Ceylon Committee, the District Judge refused to issue an interim restraining order. .",
        "The Sri Lanka Freedom Party and its officials have been named as respondents in this petition presented by the executive member of the Sri Lanka Freedom Party Mr. Montague Sarachchandra.",
        "Advocate Mr. Shantha Jayawardena, who appeared for the petitioner Mr. Montagu Sarachchandra, presented the facts and informed that there are preparations to add several amendments to the party constitution in relation to the chairmanship of the Sri Lanka Freedom Party in the upcoming meeting of the All Sri Lanka Committee of the party.",
        "Also, Mr. Shantha Jayawardena, the lawyer, informed that several more amendments are to be added to the current chairman Mr. Maithripala Sirisena to \"legitimize\" his work in that position and pointed out that the amendments to be made are totally against the party's constitution.",
        "Therefore, Mr. Shanta Jayawardena, a lawyer, also requested the court to issue an order to prevent the addition of several amendments to the party constitution in the forthcoming meeting of the All Ceylon Committee.",
        "At that time, Mr. Faizer Mustafa, the President's Attorney who appeared for the Chairman of the Sri Lanka Freedom Party, Mr. Maithripala Sirisena, stood for the respondents and strongly objected to the request of the petitioners.",
        "The President's Attorney Mr. Faizer Mustafa pointed out that the court does not have the authority to consider such a request submitted to the court regarding a party's matter and asked to reject this petition at the first instance.",
        "After considering the facts of both parties, the judge refused to issue the interim order and ordered the petition to be called again on the 5th."
      ],
